<br>
Maybe these are greedy mothers and want to deceive you since they have been trying for so long.  Similar to the test of patience the Shaman epic quest has.  You're asked to follow several times which seems in character with the quest but you hold your ground underneath the water and finally the NPC you need comes by.<br>
<br>
Gunyth say specifically that he believes the right combination of notes will produce the correct affect, but then goes on to say bring them back and give them to me.  I've gotten the objects (a few at least) from note turn ins and can't do any combining after that. Maybe the box is for the original combine and nothing more and you must:<br>
<br>
1. Turn in multiple notes simultaneously to gain spells (sort of like putting together a song). Or,<br>
<br>
2. You take the notes and attempt to combine them in the box to extract the new spells or spell parchments.<br>
<br>
Going to try both of these tonight when I get on.  <br>
<br>
I also thought they were all intertwined somehow.  Like a natural progression:<br>
<br>
1. Runes/Words produce spells<br>
2. Spells produce items<br>
3. Items produce spells<br>
<br>
That initially led me to thinking that the people that created the quest put a premium on showing the importance of general research for spell creation. Then you progressed to item creation with Gunyth and finally culminated with item extraction with Xelrin, but I think this unlikely now.  I still think research has its importance with the initial combines but beyond that I don't think there is a second combine.  <br>
<br>
